  "prompt": "Can i send my GRE scores to the four universities freely?",
  "response": "Yes, when you take the GRE, you can send your scores to up to four graduate programs for free. You need to select these programs on the test day. If you want to send your scores to additional schools or make changes after the test day, there will be a fee for each additional score report sent. Make sure to have the institution codes ready when you sit for the test, as you\u2019ll need them to direct your scores to the correct campuses and programs.",
